6jl.title: Arbital markdown demo
6jl.text:
[summary: This is a demo [1kl summary].]

This page demonstrates what can be done with [3w]. Edit this page to see the markdown used.

[toc:]

# Heading 

## Subheading 

### Subheading 

#### Subheading 

Note %%note: Note, can contain **markdown**.%%.

%%hidden(Hidden text):
Hidden *markdown* text
%%

%%%knows-requisite([1lw]):
conditional text *with* markdown
%%%

[multiple-choice(q_wants_angles): Which case fits you best?
a: I want to have a basic theoretical and practical understanding of the Bayes' rule.
-wants: [62d],[62f]
b: I can easily read algebra and don't mind the explanation moving at a fast pace. Just give me the basics, quick!
wants: [62d]
-wants: [62f]
c: I want the basics, but I'm also interested in reading more about the theoretical implications and the reasons why Bayes' rule is considered so important.
wants: [62f]
-wants: [62d]
d: I'd like to read everything! I want to have a *deep* theoretical and practical understanding of the Bayes' rule.
wants: [62d],[62f]
]

%%%wants-requisite([62d]):
%%wants-requisite([62f]):
%box:
*Your path will go over all forms of Baye's Rule, along with developing deep appreciation for its scientific usefulness. Your path will contain 12 pages:*

 * *Frequency diagrams: A first look at Bayes*
 * *Waterfall diagrams and relative odds*
 * *Introduction to Bayes' rule: Odds form*
 * *Bayes' rule: Proportional form*
 * *Extraordinary claims require extraordinary evidence*
 * *Ordinary claims require ordinary evidence*
 * *Bayes' rule: Log-odds form*
 * *Shift towards the hypothesis of least surprise*
 * *Bayes' rule: Vector form*
 * *Belief revision as probability elimination*
 * *Bayes' rule: Probability form*
 * *Bayesian view of scientific virtues*
%

%start-path([61b])%
%%
%%!wants-requisite([62f]):
%box:
No time to waste! Let's plunge directly into [693 a single-page abbreviated introduction to Bayes' rule].
%
%%
%%%

%%%!wants-requisite([62d]):
%%wants-requisite([62f]):
%box:
*Your path will teach you the basic odds form of Bayes' rule at a reasonable pace and then delve into the deep mysteries of the Bayes' Rule! Your path will contain 8 pages:*

* *Frequency diagrams: A first look at Bayes*
* *Waterfall diagrams and relative odds*
* *Introduction to Bayes' rule: Odds form*
* *Belief revision as probability elimination*
* *Extraordinary claims require extraordinary evidence*
* *Ordinary claims require ordinary evidence*
* *Shift towards the hypothesis of least surprise*
* *Bayesian view of scientific virtues*
%

%start-path([62f])%
%%

%%!wants-requisite([62f]):
%box:
*Your path will teach you the basic odds form of Bayes' rule at a reasonable pace. It will contain 3 pages:*

* *Frequency diagrams: A first look at Bayes*
* *Waterfall diagrams and relative odds*
* *Introduction to Bayes' rule: Odds form*
%

%start-path([62c])%
%%
%%%
